2. Relationship between economics and the environment, basic economic approaches to the environment
(neoclassical environmental economics, ecological economics, institutional approaches, market approaches,
etc.);
3. Environmental protection policy tools;
4. Ecosystem service concept (regulating, provisional and cultural services), different approaches to their
classification and valuation;
5. Innovative and alternative tools (payments for ecosystem services);
6. Valuation of ecosystem services, component methods (willingness to pay/accept compensation, market prices,
hedonic pricing, choice experiment, etc.);
7. Application of experiments and games in applied economics in the environmental area (flood management,
forestry, etc.);
8. Cost-benefit analysis (CBA);
9. Regulatory impact analysis in the environmental area.

